I’ve been passionate about technology since high school, when programming was a compulsory subject in my curriculum. What initially felt like just another class quickly became something much more exciting. I found myself genuinely enjoying the logic, creativity, and problem-solving involved in writing code. That early exposure inspired me to apply to the University of Information Technology and pursue a degree in Software Engineering.

